description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an experienced and capable clinical nurse specialist to provide ongoing support and a personalised service to patients with non-CF bronchiectasis and Primary Immunodeficiencies across inpatient and outpatient services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work with a complex caseload and be part of an expert team of clinicians and allied health professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need talent, dedication and an appetite to continually evaluate working practices to ensure a safe and quality service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported in your role by a lead clinical nurse specialist (CF) who will assist you with audit, research and in developing a national profile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If the prospect of this challenge excites you, please apply. For more information or an informal chat please contact Alan Peres: Lead Clinical Nurse Specialist: a.peres@rbht.nhs.uk.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
